Maiada's work deals with ways that social and religious structures interconnect and influence the individual. Using endurance art, Maiada's interest in social issues draws on a unique and personal perspective.

Maiada, born in Palestine( Arab Israeli), and graduated from Bar Ilan University in criminology and sociology then obtained another degree in art at Haifa university, received her education in the UK, where she completed her Masters from Coventry university, and currently finishing her PhD at Sheffield Hallam university.

Her study attempts to connect the textual analysis to the individual’s social experience by way of using performance and relating it to culture and social life. 
The intention is to investigate cultural identity using performance, and with the purpose to establish if these performances are linked to collective identities. 

Significance of the research;
Studies of this kind have been carried out before through western performances but the significance here is that the culture to which it relates is very different from the European and western cultures. The values and norms of the Middle Eastern culture can create an obstacle for non-Middle Eastern viewer in understanding the work nature, culture, and what motivates the performer.

Specialties
Endurance art - reflection on the body in Palestinian art, sexuality, gender, taboos, restrictions, femininity, and exile.
